;
The peptide bond between residues 23 and 24 is in the cis conformation. 
The four amino acids (G,N,S,S) at the carboxyl-terminus  result from the
cloning procedure. Also a mutation of the first amino acid (MET1) into 
a proline is a result of the cloning procedure.
;

